    "Hotel Management System\n",
    "This Hotel Management System is a web-based application designed to streamline hotel operations, including booking, customer management, and service tracking. Built with Django, it provides an intuitive interface for users and administrators to interact with the system efficiently.\n",
    "\n",
    "Features\n",
    "User Functionalities\n",
    "Room Booking: Book rooms based on availability.\n",
    "User Registration and Login: Secure sign-up and login functionality.\n",
    "Profile Management: Users can manage their personal information.\n",
    "View Bookings: Access current and past bookings.\n",
    "Admin Functionalities\n",
    "Room Management: Add, update, or delete room details.\n",
    "Booking Management: View and manage customer bookings.\n",
    "Customer Management: Access customer profiles and booking history.\n",
    "General Features\n",
    "Dynamic Pricing: Update room rates based on demand.\n",
    "Responsive Design: Accessible on desktop and mobile devices.\n",
    "Secure Data Handling: Implements Django’s authentication and CSRF protection.\n",
    "Technologies Used\n",
    "Backend: Django (Python)\n",
    "Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript\n",
    "Database: SQLite (default), easily configurable for PostgreSQL or MySQL\n",
    "Styling: Bootstrap and custom CSS\n",
    "Hosting: Compatible with platforms like Heroku or AWS\n",
    "Installation\n",
    "Clone the repository:\n",
    "\n",
    "bash\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "git clone <repo>\n",
    "cd HotelManagementSystem\n",
    "Create and activate a virtual environment:\n",
    "\n",
    "bash\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "python -m venv venv\n",
    "source venv/bin/activate  \n",
    "Install dependencies:\n",
    "\n",
    "bash\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "pip install -r requirements.txt\n",
    "Apply database migrations:\n",
    "\n",
    "bash\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "python manage.py makemigrations\n",
    "python manage.py migrate\n",
    "Run the development server:\n",
    "\n",
    "bash\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "python manage.py runserver\n",
    "Open your browser and go to http://127.0.0.1:8000.\n",
    "\n",
    "Project Structure\n",
    "csharp\n",
    "Copy code\n",
    "HotelManagementSystem/\n",
    "│\n",
    "├── hotelapp/               # Main application folder\n",
    "│   ├── static/             # Static assets (CSS, JS, images)\n",
    "│   ├── templates/          # HTML templates\n",
    "│   ├── views.py            # Application logic\n",
    "│   ├── models.py           # Database models\n",
    "│   ├── urls.py             # URL configurations\n",
    "│   └── forms.py            # Django forms\n",
    "│\n",
    "├── db.sqlite3              # SQLite database\n",
    "├── manage.py               # Django management script\n",
    "├── requirements.txt        # Python dependencies\n",
    "└── README.md               # Project documentation\n",
    "Usage\n",
    "Admin Panel: Access the admin panel at /admin to manage rooms and users.\n",
    "User Functions: Register, login, and book rooms via the provided forms.\n",
    "Room Management: View room availability and update details through the admin interface.\n",
    "Future Enhancements\n",
    "Payment Gateway Integration: Add online payment options.\n",
    "Multi-Language Support: Enable translations for international users.\n",
    "Analytics Dashboard: Provide insights into bookings and revenue.\n",
    "Notifications: Email and SMS alerts for bookings and updates.\n",
